Flaggers will control traffic in the intersection of Chinden Boulevard and Linder Road tonight (April 22) for the installation of traffic signal poles. During this time crews will also reduce eastbound lanes entering the Linder intersection. This configuration will remain in place for the duration of construction anticipated for later this summer when this segment between Linder and Meridian Road will open to four lanes two in each direction with a center median. Eastbound traffic at Linder will be reduced from two through lanes one dedicated right and one dedicated left to one through-right lane and one dedicated left. The westbound traffic configuration will not be impacted. Eastbound motorists should expect significant delays at peak travel time and allow extra time to reach their destination.
